  "text": "For a non-founder individual i, let be the probability that the QTL allele at chromosome j of indi-vidual i is inherited from the QTL allele at chromosome x of its father; and let probability that allele at chromosome j is inherited from the chromosome y of its mother. In the absence of marker information, these are 0.5. Assume that these probabilities have been computed, conditional on all marker information (m), using one of several methods [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . We will refer to these probabilities as PDQ's (probability of descent for a QTL allele) [CITATION_6] ; they can be put together in a row vector w i, j (while each PDQ is a conditional probability, we do not explicitly include m in the notation for simplicity in the following expressions).",
